# Tooling & Quality Gates

Before considering a change done, it must pass:

```bash
npm run lint        # ESLint (flat config, eslint.config.js)
npm run format      # Prettier write (or format:check in CI)
npm run typecheck   # tsc --noEmit
npm run build       # tsc && vite build
```

- A husky `pre-commit` hook runs `lint-staged` + `typecheck`. Never bypass it
  with `--no-verify`.
- ESLint is the source of truth for code rules; Prettier owns formatting
  (`eslint-config-prettier` disables conflicting style rules).
- Prefix intentionally-unused vars/args with `_` to satisfy `no-unused-vars`.
- Don't add comments that just narrate code. Comment intent, trade-offs, or
  non-obvious constraints only.
